|{{flag|Israel}}
|[[Yom Ha'atzmaut]]
|{{sort|05-14|Iyar&amp;nbsp;5  &lt;small&gt;(On or between Apr 15 and May 15, depending on the [[Hebrew calendar]]).&lt;/small&gt;}}
|{{sort|1948|1948}}
|[[United Kingdom]] and the [[British Mandate for Palestine (legal instrument)|British Mandate for Palestine]]
|[[Israeli Declaration of Independence]] on May 14, 1948 (5&amp;nbsp;Iyar 5708 in the [[Hebrew calendar]]). [[Yom Ha'atzmaut]] is celebrated on the Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday nearest to 5&amp;nbsp;Iyar, so it occurs between 3&amp;nbsp;and 6&amp;nbsp;Iyar each year; this means that the holiday can fall any time between and including April 15 and May 15, according to the [[Gregorian calendar]].
